        "feedback": "The base plate and standoff posts are correctly dimensioned and positioned. However, the pilot holes are missing from the posts. The rendered images and volume metrics reveal only a single hole drilled through the flat center of the plate, leaving all 6 posts completely solid. This occurred because `result.faces(\">Z\").workplane().hole(hole_diameter)` creates a single workplane positioned at the center of the bounding box of all selected top faces, resulting in one central hole. To fix this, you must generate the grid points again on the top workplane before drilling. For example, call `.rarray(grid_spacing_x, grid_spacing_y, grid_count_x, grid_count_y)` on the Z=15 workplane prior to calling `.hole(hole_diameter)`.",
